pressure fell by 4.8 to 6.5 mm Hg with tirzepatide versus 3.6 mm Hg with semaglutide, and diastolic blood
pressure fell by 1.9 to 2.9 mm Hg versus 1.0 mm Hg. Pulse rose modestly and similarly with tirzepatide and
semaglutide, generally by about 2 to 3 beats per minute by week 40. In SURPASS-4 and SURPASS-CVOT,
triglycerides and systolic blood pressure also moved modestly in favor of tirzepatide. 
